#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""joe: a local-first interactive agent shell, modelled on Claude Code.

Pairs a personalised orchestrator model with a Claude-Code-style
interactive shell: persistent REPL, file Read/Write/Edit tools, shell
access, grep/glob, conversation memory, slash commands, and code-
generation delegation to a separate coder model so the heavier model
writes the actual code while the orchestrator handles meta-work.

Why not just `ollama run <model>`? Because that's a chat REPL with no
filesystem access. This adds tools, file edits, shell execution, syntax-
highlighted diffs, a delegation contract, subagents, cross-session
memory, scheduled jobs, voice/vision input, and seven "outstanding-tier"
features (self-training, smart inbox, model-drift eval, live pair-
programming, knowledge graph, cross-machine sync, end-of-day reflection).

Usage:
  joe                  start the REPL
  joe -p "prompt"      one-shot: run a single prompt, exit
  joe -s <name>        resume / save a named session
  joe --coder qwen2.5-coder:7b   override the delegate-coder model

Default models assume `joe-gemma` (a Modelfile-personalised gemma3:4b)
plus `qwen2.5-coder:7b/14b`. Swap with --model / --coder or via the
JOE_DEFAULT_MODEL / JOE_DEFAULT_CODER env vars.
"""

